  <span id="freeText4026856866319755874" style="display:none">I put this book on my TBR list many years ago. My goal of late is to read some titles that have been on that list since I first joined GRs in 2013. My interest in this book was because it said it was a book about the Taj Mahal. I love reading historical fiction novels where I can get wrapped up in the place and time and learn something new in the process. I didn’t learn a lot about the Taj Mahal in this novel. It’s more of a love story... yes between man and women but much more family , friendship, culture and faith. A rewarding read even if some parts seemed unbelievable. </span>
