<div id="review_7054449" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/7054449" />
    <a title="Sara Register" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/427596-sara-register"><img alt="Sara Register" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447259217p2/427596.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/7054449?book_show_action=true">Sep 30, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sara Register" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sara Register" href="/user/show/427596-sara-register">Sara Register</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/427596-sara-register?shelf=novels">novels</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/427596-sara-register?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7054449" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6634412264551549730">I found this book pretty fascinating as well as disturbing...and not in a good way. I have noticed that since having children, I don&apos;t do well with violence in books. This book has some pretty blatant violence in it that was hard for me to read. (I&apos;m sure it really isn&apos;t THAT bad, I just am ultra sensitive to it, especially when it has to do with children--there is a lot of castration and war and executions etc...) I had to read another &quot;light&quot; book while reading this one because it affected me </span>
  <span id="freeText6634412264551549730" style="display:none">I found this book pretty fascinating as well as disturbing...and not in a good way. I have noticed that since having children, I don't do well with violence in books. This book has some pretty blatant violence in it that was hard for me to read. (I'm sure it really isn't THAT bad, I just am ultra sensitive to it, especially when it has to do with children--there is a lot of castration and war and executions etc...) I had to read another "light" book while reading this one because it affected me so much. John Shors does a great job however of painting a vivid picture of India during the time of the building of the Taj Mahal. He also does a great job of writing characters that you feel you actually get to know. You really love the good guys and you really despise the bad guys. I love books like that, where the characters come to life. If you are wanting a book with great closure and a happy ending though, don't look here.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6634412264551549730" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

