<span id="freeTextContainer10508576199505359768">3.5 stars <br/>One day, Jahanara realizes that it is time to tell the story of her past to her two young granddaughters. As they listen intently, their grandmother spins the tale of a young girl well- loved by her parents, the Emperor and Empress of Hindustan in the 17th century. Jahanara recalls the years of her childhood when she and her four brothers and two sisters were sheltered by the love of their parents. But not everything can stay exactly as we expect it to and as the years go by, Jahanara </span>
  <span id="freeText10508576199505359768" style="display:none">3.5 stars <br />One day, Jahanara realizes that it is time to tell the story of her past to her two young granddaughters. As they listen intently, their grandmother spins the tale of a young girl well- loved by her parents, the Emperor and Empress of Hindustan in the 17th century. Jahanara recalls the years of her childhood when she and her four brothers and two sisters were sheltered by the love of their parents. But not everything can stay exactly as we expect it to and as the years go by, Jahanara describes the loss of her mother, a loveless marriage, and the battling brothers who could tear down an entire empire. Plenty of action and romance in this one that all sets up for a background that also sees the illustrious Taj Mahal being built. <br /><br /><br />This book has it all- action, romance, friendship, family and above all a woman's devotion to the empire and its people.</span>
