 rejected years ago and thought she\'d never have to face again: clairvoyance. Suddenly, Mariela\'s visions come swiftly and unbidden, as do revelations about her other tenants. Lost loves, hidden yearnings, old jealousies all reside on Calle Ocho. Most of all, Mariela\'s second sight awakens her not just to the truth about Hector\'s death and the secrets in others lives but to the possibilities blooming within her own.\n\nWith warmth, wit, and insight, award-winning author Anjanette Delgado explores one woman\'s flawed but heartfelt attempt to live and love well, transporting listeners to the center of contemporary Little Havana and a community of uniquely human, unforgettable characters.&quot;<\/span>\n  <a data-text-id=\"8769985738945473900\" href=\"#\" onclick=\"swapContent(\$(this));; return false;\">...more<\/a>\n\n    <\/div>\n\n      <div class=\'wtrButtonContainer wtrSignedOut\' id=\'17_book_19083227\'>\n<div class=\'wtrUp wtrLeft\'>\n<form action=\"/shelf/add_to_shelf\" accept-charset=\"UTF-8\" method=\"post\"><input name=\"utf8\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"&#x2713;\" /><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"authenticity_token\" value=\"bfEhPWxr0PwO3AYC+AEGHCjzzjEV/2Q/oILf5K/HyXVwpmTUOuQOwx/ygzn5/8t825SW0zBHmfhJrkblXyQcyg==\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"book_id\" id=\"book_id\" value=\"19083227\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"name\" id=\"name\" value=\"to-read\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"unique_id\" id=\"unique_id\" value=\"17_book_19083227\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"wtr_new\" id=\"wtr_new\" value=\"true\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"from_choice\" id=\"from_choice\" value=\"false\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"from_home_module\" id=\"from_home_module\" value=\"false\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"ref\" id=\"ref\" value=\"\" class=\"wtrLeftUpRef\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"existing_review\" id=\"existing_review\" value=\"false\" class=\"wtrExisting\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"book_origin\" id=\"book_origin\" va